From 2c4df60b43795ae2974384ddb569a9dee5ddca35 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dirk-Jan Faber <dfaber@victronenergy.com>
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 2026 19:43:36 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix(switch): various node status text fixes

- doc fix: a numeric input switch does not use "Value", only "Dimming"
- refactor updateSwitchStatus() to encapsulate a temporary status message
- updates to virtual switches' properties are not debounced any more. This simplifies the implementation of the previous item.
- Do not output "nodeInstances" in case debug output is activated, this fixes excessively long debug output
- virtual bilge pump, display state 0x00 as "Auto" instead of "Off"
- virtual bilge pump, Status of 0x00 is "Not running", not "Off"
- small formatting fixes in updateSwitchStatus(), e.g. don't display "Value" for a numeric input switch
- define / move "stateKey" and "statusKey" to an outer scope to keep string constants a bit more DRY
---
